  "text": "Our investigation of this issue employed data from the Treatment Strategies in Schizophrenia (TSS) study [CITATION_1] , in which all inpatients with clinical diagnoses of schizophrenia or schizophreniform or schizoaffective disorder at five sites varying in clinical organization and patient population were screened. There were 6,012 patients screened for the study, and only 528 (9%) entered [CITATION_2] . This degree of selectivity certainly suggests that selection biases need to be investigated.",
